{{Quote|Why the Alliance would let its most ''renowned leader'' risk her life attempting to recruit some broken, useless former historian ''eludes'' me... I'll let you explain ''that'' to the ''Emperor...'' when I deliver you ''personally''!|Orman Tagge|<ref name="Date" />}}
'''''Star Wars'' 30''' is the thirtieth issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of [[Star Wars comic books|comics]].

==Plot summary==
[[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] travels to [[Metalorn/Legends|Metalorn]] on a mission to spread the message of hope to its residents. Metalorn, a factory [[Planet/Legends|planet]], has been completely controlled by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] under the direction of [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Corwyth]] with no information of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] reaching its citizens. Leia manages to evade Imperial [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] long enough to contact her former instructor [[Arn Horada]] in order to have him spread the word that the Rebel Alliance is actively opposing the Empire's tyranny. She is quickly confronted by [[Baron/Legends|Baron]] [[Orman Tagge/Legends|Orman Tagge]] before she is able to establish any details, but manages to escape with the help of a youngster named [[Tammia Hollusen|Tammi]].

